org.apache.hadoop.hbase.io.crypto.tls

Class BaseX509ParameterizedTestCase

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.hadoop.hbase.io.crypto.tls.BaseX509ParameterizedTestCase
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    TestTlsIPC, TestX509Util

    public abstract class BaseX509ParameterizedTestCase
extends Object
    Base class for parameterized unit tests that use X509TestContext for testing different X509 parameter combinations (CA key type, cert key type, with/without a password, with/without hostname verification, etc). This base class takes care of setting up / cleaning up the test environment, and caching the X509TestContext objects used by the tests.

    This file has been copied from the Apache ZooKeeper project.

      • cachedTestContexts

        protected static Map<Integer,X509TestContext> cachedTestContexts
        Because key generation and writing / deleting files is kind of expensive, we cache the certs and on-disk files between test cases. None of the test cases modify any of this data so it's safe to reuse between tests. This caching makes all test cases after the first one for a given parameter combination complete almost instantly.
